&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-403&quot; title=&quot;Failover handler doesn&amp;#39;t release pending tasks that could complete on connection drop&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-403&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-403&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Trigger whenOffline event on queued requests on drop&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the handle connection failure method runs it should trigger the&lt;br/&gt;
when off line behavior of any currently queued tasks in order to allow&lt;br/&gt;
timely completion of requests that do not need to wait for a new&lt;br/&gt;
connection to happen such as session close, message acknowledge etc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
